  "prompt": "What are big v telecoms consumer complaint and reviews?",
  "response": "Big V Telecom is a provider of cloud telephony services, such as IVR systems, call tracking, and bulk SMS services. User reviews and consumer complaints can vary widely and may depend on individual experiences. Below are common themes that might be found in both positive and negative feedback for a company like Big V Telecom:\n\n### Positive Reviews:\n1. **Ease of Use**: Many users appreciate how user-friendly the interface and setup processes are for the services offered.\n2. **Customer Support**: Positive reviews often highlight responsive and helpful customer service teams.\n3. **Reliability**: Customers may appreciate consistent uptime and reliable performance of cloud telephony services.\n4. **Cost-Effectiveness**: Competitive pricing and value for money can be a common praise among satisfied users.\n5. **Feature-Rich**: Users often commend the broad range of features available, from call recording to detailed analytics and reporting.\n\n### Negative Reviews:\n1. **Technical Issues**: Complaints may involve technical glitches or outages that disrupt services.\n2. **Customer Service**: Negative feedback can stem from unresponsive or unhelpful customer support experiences.\n3. **Billing Discrepancies**: Issues related to billing, such as unexpected charges or difficulties in resolving billing disputes, could be common.\n4. **Complexity in Advanced Features**: Some users might find advanced features complex or challenging to implement without support.\n5. **Limited Customization**: Certain users may feel the need for more customizable options to better fit their specific business needs.\n\n### Common Complaint Areas:\n1. **Downtime**: Some consumers might experience and report downtime, which impacts their business operations.\n2. **Integration Issues**: Problems integrating with other software or systems could be a frequent point of contention.\n3. **Response Time**: Delayed responses from customer support or technical assistance, especially during critical issues, can be frustrating for consumers.\n\nFor the most current and specific information, it would be best to refer to recent reviews on consumer feedback platforms like Google Reviews, Trustpilot, or specialized telecom review websites.",
